external_knowledge:
- "Service facilities" are facilities that provide specific services to the community or other entities.;
- "Cumulative level" in this context refers to the sum of the hierarchical levels of facilities within the same country, ordered by facility name.;
- "More than 100 samples a day" indicates a high processing capacity, suggesting a well-equipped and possibly large facility.;

- "Top-rated" refers to facilities with the highest average ratings in their respective countries;
- "Facility count" is the total number of facilities in a country;
- "Average rating" is the mean rating given to the facilities in a country.

- 'Sequencing' refers to genomic sequencing services;
- 'High daily capacity' implies the facility can process more than 100 samples per day;
- 'More than five staff members' indicates the facility has a sufficient team to handle operations.

- 'Multiple services' refers to facilities offering at least 2 services;
- 'Highly rated' means facilities with an average rating greater than 3.5;
- 'Frequently accessed' means facilities accessed by at least 5 users;
- 'Significant sample processing capacity' means facilities capable of processing more than 500 samples per day.

- A left join is used to include all facilities, even those without any staff members;
- Facilities without staff will have a count of 0 for staff members, which is included in the average calculation;
- The result is a floating-point number to represent the average accurately.

sql:
SELECT CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN s.staff_id IS NOT NULL THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) / COUNT(f.facility_id) AS average_staff_per_facility
FROM facilities f
LEFT JOIN staff s ON f.facility_id = s.facility_id;

